Summary of THg, MeHg, and LOI model results

KVITENSE

2023-03-21

Below, model results are presented for THg responses, MeHg responses, and LOI responses. A table of ranked predictors for each model is at the bottom of the document.

THg models

log(THg) model without LOI

  • Harvards GEOS-Chem WetLoss variables dropped in relative importance compared to the first iteration of this model after a couple redundant predictors were removed and missing data were re-imputed.
  • Top predictors are pH, GEOS-Chem predictors, catchment characteristics (temp, precip, clay/sand, runoff, elevation, etc.), conductivity, etc..
  • ~25 predictors
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.28
  • Minimum MAE: 0.182

log(THg) model with LOI included

  • LOI is now top predictor, then pH, and then the story is pretty similar to the situation above, with some reordering of top predictors. Some of these predictors are highly correlated, and we may not be able to tease out exact rankings relative to one another.
  • This THg model with LOI included has better predictive accuracy than without LOI and requires fewer predictors.
  • Results and interpretation seem cleaner for this model relative to THg/LOI below because were accounting for LOI, but predictors for LOI are not mixed in with predictors for THg
  • ~14 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.247
  • Minimum MAE: 0.158

log(THg/LOI) model

  • Interesting non-monotonic pattern in RMSE as predictors are removed - likely because some predictors are better for predicting THg vs.LOI.
  • RMSE seems to start to decline again when predictors associated with LOI but not THg are removed (around 8-11 preds): SN, NH4, InorgNWetDep, NO3.
  • Hg0DryDep is top predictor for THg/LOI - Hg0DryDep and HgPDryDep rose in importance relative to the WetLoss predictors
  • Elevation also rose in relative importance
  • Takes more variables to maintain best predictive performance, likely because we are predicting both THg and LOI, and LOI models show that more predictors are needed for LOI relative to THg.
  • ~ 29 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.268
  • Minimum MAE: 0.173

MeHg models

log(MeHg) model with THg & LOI included

  • THg, LOI are top predictors, followed by temperature, precipitation, clay, BFI (ratio of base flow to total flow), conductivity, OM, oxygen, chl-a, developed land cover, depth
  • GEOS-Chem predictors are not important when THg and LOI are included
  • Unsure what PctNonAgIntrodManagVegCat and PctImpCat are - look up
  • ~ 15 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.307
  • Minimum MAE: 0.236

log(MeHg) model WITHOUT THg & LOI included

  • Without THg & LOI included, pH is top predictor, followed by clay, OM, forest cover, temperature, etc.
  • GEOS-Chem predictors become important when THg & LOI are removed
  • Some new predictors also pop up (NO3, d180, zooplankton, etc.)
  • Worse prediction accuracy w/o THG & LOI and takes more predictors to maintain best performance
  • ~ 27 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.354
  • Minimum MAE: 0.272

log(MeHg/THg) model with LOI included

  • Top predictor is temperature, followed by a couple GEOS-Chem predictors, elevation, precipitation, chl-a, secchi, runoff, NH4, depth, land use/cover, etc.
  • GEOS-Chem predictors are more important in predicting MeHg/THg relative to predicting just MeHg
  • LOI is not very important in predicting MeHg/THg (25th in importance)
  • ~ 25 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.327
  • Minimum MAE: 0.251

log(MeHg/THg) model WITHOUT LOI included

  • Very similar results as previous model with LOI included because LOI was not very important in model above
  • ~ 23 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.328
  • Minimum MAE: 0.252

LOI models

log(LOI) model with GEOS-Chem predictors

  • Top 6 predictors are non-GEOS-Chem predictors
  • More predictors are generally retained for LOI than THg, probably because the GEOS-Chem variables are strong predictors of THg and less so for LOI.
  • Note that iterative removal of GEOS-Chem predictors doesnt usually strongly impact predictive accuracy.
  • ~24 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.234
  • Minimum MAE: 0.16

log(LOI) w/ GEOS-Chem removed

  • Top 6 predictors are the exact same as above (all non-GEOS-Chem predictors), and the rest of the order is very similar if the GEOS-Chem predictors are ignored.
  • Note that removal of GEOS-Chem predictors doesnt impact best predictive accuracy for LOI.
  • ~23 vars
  • Minimum RMSE: 0.234
  • Minimum MAE: 0.159
